Do not order pickup online on May 5th

I am not sure about the food quality, but as far as the staff I couldn’t feel more disrespected than I felt today, April 10, 2020.  I arrived at the restaurant to pick up an online order two minutes after the order was due.  The restaurant did set up a plastic shelf outside the inner door, and keep that door locked at all times due to COVID precautions. At first glance I did not see my order at the shelf.  Maybe two minutes later a light skin employee with a hat came outside the door to place some more bags at the shelf. I’ve tried to inquire him of how long he estimated my order would take to get ready. He was very rude and said “if your order is not at the shelf they are working on it”. This is was not my question, but ok, I kept waiting.  Maybe after around 15 minutes of wait, and maybe ten another bags in the shelf I inquired him again, and he limited to say the order was coming.  40 minutes passed by and every time I inquired he answered: “it’s coming up”.  After around one hour of wait I needed to ask him a little harsher since my politeness was apparently not working. For the first time, maybe out of a little of common sense in his mind, he decided to question the kitchen staff about my order, being responded they did not have any order with that name to be prepared. As it might be imaginable it was completely overwhelming that answer.  During the whole time what I noticed was the whole staff with no mask at all, laughing, joking and listening to loud music while preparing other people’s food, and the total lack of respect with the customer that was there waiting for around one hour.  I’ve tried to complain with some sort of manager, but couldn’t even figure out who it was, and to me no sort of attention was directed whatsoever.  Disrespect and lack of professionalism is everything I could notice in this visit. This is my second google review in a lifetime, I really don’t like doing that, but today I felt obligated to show my frustration so this maybe get to some owner attention.

So there's very few Korean places in Detroit so when we visited Chicago we took a chance on a Korean Mexican fusion place and damn it was a good gamble! My wife and I got the chicken tacos and a bulgogi beef burrito plus fried rice and sweet potato waffle fries. The helpful staff told us the Seoul sauces were the best part of the dishes and they were dead on. Spicy and a little sweet the fried rice was a surprising change from traditional Spanish rice. The ambience of the shop was decidedly urban with street art, multicolor boom boxes, and headphones on the walls. The radio playlist rolled through Wu Tang Clan and Snoop and we were nodding throughout our whole meal. Definitely coming back.
